---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { CAL_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who I am and what I write about here."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-07-07')}
	aiUsage="assisted"
>
	<p>Hey - I'm Asif.</p>

	<p>
		I've been building software for 15+ years: frontend, backend, emails, infra,
		data, mobile. I've done all of it, but I'm still a backend engineer at heart.
	</p>

	<p>
		Right now I build AI software at a venture firm: CRM, agents, internal tools,
		and a LOT of plumbing. I'm the engineer responsible for making the firm more
		efficient, so it's part maintaining a product that's over 5 years old and
		part building workflows people didn't even know they wanted.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm shipping random workflows daily and getting a little AI psychosis with my
		builds. Look, being a solo developer is really a trip.
	</p>

	<p>This blog is where I post tips and notes for later reference.</p>

	<p>
		Mostly, though, I want to find the people ACTUALLY using AI to do real work,
		not the performative version. That's the whole point of putting this out
		there.
	</p>

	<p>
		I swear I'm working on reducing my default cynical nature and trying to be
		more of an optimist.
	</p>

	<p>
		If any of that resonates, <a href={CAL_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">book 15
		minutes with me</a> to talk tech or philosophy or leadership.
	</p>
</Layout>
